        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 1 at 4:02PM CDT by NWS Louisville KY</headline>
        <description>At 402 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles south of Morgantown, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Anderson, Gasper, Browning, Davis Crossroads, Sharer, Buffalo Fork,
Chandlers Chapel, Costelow, and Richelieu.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
